---
// src/pages/services/dryer-repair/takes-too-long.astro
// Phase B-2 v2.1 — Dryer Takes Too Long sub-service. Failure-mode pattern.
// VENT cleaning emphasis + LA fire safety angle (NFPA, LAFD lint fire stats).
// $89 residential, BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 #1346255700410. 4 schema entities.
// Em-dash budget: ≤2.

import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/dryer-repair/takes-too-long/";

const title = "Dryer Takes Too Long Repair LA — Same Day";
const description = "Dryer running 2 to 3 cycles? Vent restriction is the cause 80% of the time, and a fire risk. LA same-day diagnostic + vent clearance. BHGS #A49573.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why is my dryer taking 2 hours to dry one load?",
    a: "About 80% of the time it's a restricted dryer vent, not a failed component. The vent is the path that hot, moist air takes from the dryer to the outside of your house. As lint accumulates inside the vent over years, the airflow drops. The dryer compensates by running longer, but eventually the load comes out damp because the moist air has nowhere to go. We clear the vent on every long-cycle call we make and confirm airflow with an anemometer before we leave."
  },
  {
    q: "Is a clogged dryer vent really a fire hazard?",
    a: "Yes, and the LAFD takes it seriously. The US Fire Administration tracks roughly 2,900 dryer fires per year nationally with lint accumulation as the leading cause. In our LA service area we see vents that have not been cleaned in 8 to 15 years routinely — the lint inside is dense enough to ignite from the dryer's heating element if airflow drops below a critical threshold. This is why we include vent inspection on every long-cycle call. It is not optional in our diagnostic."
  },
  {
    q: "How often should I clean my dryer vent?",
    a: "Once per year for a typical LA household with daily laundry. More often (every 6 months) if you have multiple people, pets, or a long vent run (over 25 feet). The lint trap inside the dryer catches maybe 60% of the lint produced. The rest goes into the vent, where it accumulates at predictable rates. Our LA vent clearance ranges from $145 to $245 depending on length and access."
  },
  {
    q: "Is it the vent or is it a heating problem?",
    a: "Both produce long cycle times. We test by measuring exterior vent airflow first. Below 1,500 feet per minute means vent restriction is the primary issue. Normal airflow plus long cycle time points to a failing heating component (usually a heating element starting to short, or a thermistor giving the control board bad readings). We test both at the diagnostic visit, in that order."
  },
  {
    q: "What does vent clearance involve?",
    a: "We disconnect the dryer at the wall, run a rotating brush through the vent line from the dryer side, vacuum the lint out as we go, and verify airflow at the exterior cap. If the exterior cap has a damper or bird guard that is restricting flow, we replace it. On vent runs over 25 feet or with multiple bends, we may need to clean from both ends. Standard residential vent clearance runs 45 to 90 minutes."
  },
  {
    q: "What if vent clearance doesn't fix the long cycle?",
    a: "Then the cause is a failing heating component or a faulty moisture sensor. About 15 to 20% of long-cycle calls fall in this category. We test the heating element ohms, the thermistor or moisture sensor reading, and the control board output. The most common second-cause repair is a heating element that has degraded but not yet fully failed (still produces some heat, but at reduced output). Replacement runs $285 to $425."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "Ninety days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. If the same component fails within 90 days, we replace it free. BHGS #A49573 and BBB Accredited Business. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. Vent clearance carries a 12-month workmanship warranty."
  }
];

