    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Dryer Vent Clearance and Long Cycle Repair",
    "name": "Dryer Takes Too Long Diagnostic and Vent Clearance",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Residential dryer long-cycle diagnostic and vent clearance across all five SoCal counties. Vent restriction is the leading cause of long cycle times and a documented fire hazard per US Fire Administration. Vent inspection, brush clearance, exterior cap inspection, airflow verification with anemometer. Heating element, thermistor, moisture sensor, and control board secondary diagnostics. Whirlpool, GE, Samsung, LG, Maytag, Electrolux, Bosch, Frigidaire, KitchenAid, Miele, Thermador and other major brands. $89 residential diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Dryer Repair", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/dryer-repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Dryer Takes Too Long", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="Vent Clearance + Long Cycle Diagnostic · LA · OC · Ventura · IE"
  title="Dryer Takes Too Long Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle={`One load taking 2 to 3 cycles? Restricted vent is the cause 80% of the time, and an LAFD-tracked fire hazard. Same-day vent clearance and component diagnostic. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Dryer Long Cycle Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Long-cycle diagnostic</p>
    <h2>If a load is taking 2 to 3 cycles, the cause is almost always the vent. And it's a fire risk worth taking seriously.</h2>

    <p>A dryer that takes far longer than it used to is the third most common service call we make in LA. The dryer heats normally, the drum tumbles, but loads come out damp at the end of the cycle and need a second or third run. About 80% of these calls trace to a restricted dryer vent. The remaining 20% are heating components that are degrading but have not fully failed yet.</p>

    <p>This service call is a fire safety call as much as it is a performance call. The US Fire Administration tracks roughly 2,900 residential dryer fires per year nationally with lint accumulation as the leading ignition source. In LA, we routinely see vents that have not been cleaned in 8 to 15 years on homes built in the 1970s and 1980s, and the lint density inside those vents is enough to ignite if dryer airflow drops below a critical threshold and the cabinet overheats. Our techs treat every long-cycle call as a fire-prevention visit.</p>

    <p>$89 residential diagnostic, waived with repair. Vent clearance starts at $145. BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. We service all major brands: Whirlpool, GE, Samsung, LG, Maytag, Electrolux, Bosch, Frigidaire, KitchenAid, Miele, Thermador, Speed Queen, and others.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LA FIRE SAFETY -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">LA fire safety angle</p>
    <h2>Why a clogged vent matters more in LA than most cities.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three factors make dryer vent fires a particular issue in our service area.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Aging housing stock with original vent runs</h3>
    <p>A large share of LA single-family homes were built between 1950 and 1985, and many of those still have the original dryer vent runs. We've cleared vents in West LA, Pasadena, and the San Fernando Valley that had never been professionally cleaned in 25+ years. The lint accumulation in those runs was not just a performance issue; it was a fire ready to start.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Long vent runs in second-story laundry rooms</h3>
    <p>LA homes built since 2000 often have laundry on the second floor with vent runs of 25 to 40 feet routed through interior walls. Long runs accumulate lint faster because every bend in the run creates a turbulence point where fibers settle. These vents need clearance every 6 to 9 months, not annually.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Stackable units in condos and apartments</h3>
    <p>Stackable washer-dryer combos in LA condos often have vent runs hidden behind drywall with no easy access. The vent run is part of the building, not the unit, which means HOA approval is sometimes needed for full clearance. We work with HOA management on these calls and document the work for resident files.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">What we look for during clearance</h3>
    <p>Brittle foil flex hose (replace with rigid metal duct), crushed sections behind the dryer (typical when the dryer was pushed back hard against the wall), bird nests in exterior vent caps (very common in our coverage area, especially in spring), and dampers that have rusted shut. Each of these compounds the lint problem.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 DIAGNOSTIC -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Diagnostic order</p>
    <h2>How we diagnose long cycles in 30 to 45 minutes.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Exterior vent airflow test.</strong> We measure airflow at the exterior vent cap with the dryer running on high heat. Above 1,500 feet per minute is normal. Between 800 and 1,500 is restricted. Below 800 is severely restricted and a fire risk.</li>
      <li><strong>Lint trap inspection.</strong> Quick visual to make sure the homeowner's screen is clean and undamaged. Tear in the screen lets lint past into the blower housing.</li>
      <li><strong>Vent line inspection.</strong> Disconnect at the dryer, look down the vent run with a borescope or strong flashlight. Heavy lint accumulation visible within the first 6 feet means the entire run needs clearance.</li>
      <li><strong>Brush clearance with vacuum capture.</strong> Rotating brush through the vent run, multiple passes if needed. Vacuum captures the dislodged lint as it comes out. We pull lint out in batches and weigh it for the customer record on long runs.</li>
      <li><strong>Exterior cap inspection.</strong> Check the damper, bird guard, and rodent guard. Replace if rusted or restricting flow.</li>
      <li><strong>Post-clearance airflow verification.</strong> Re-measure airflow after clearance. Normal reading confirms the vent is the issue. Still-low reading after thorough clearance points to a damaged duct that needs replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Heating component test (if vent is clear and cycles are still long).</strong> Heating element ohms, thermistor reading, moisture sensor reading, control board output verification.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 PRICING -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2>What long-cycle repairs and vent clearance cost.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $89 (residential), waived with repair or vent clearance.</p>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$89, waived with service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Standard vent clearance (single-story, run under 15 feet)</td><td>$145 to $185</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Long-run vent clearance (over 15 feet, second-story laundry)</td><td>$185 to $245</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Vent clearance plus exterior cap replacement</td><td>$185 to $285</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Foil flex hose replacement (behind dryer, code-compliant rigid metal)</td><td>$85 to $125</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Full vent run replacement (drywall access required)</td><td>Quoted on-site, typical $385 to $725</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Heating element replacement (if vent clear)</td><td>$285 to $425</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermistor or moisture sensor replacement</td><td>$145 to $245</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Vent clearance workmanship warranty</td><td>12 months</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Repair parts and labor warranty</td><td>90 days</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Brand notes</p>
    <h2>Long-cycle patterns by brand.</h2>

    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Whirlpool, Maytag, KitchenAid (Whirlpool family).</strong> Long-cycle calls almost always trace to vent. Heating element starts to degrade at year 8 to 10 on units with restricted vents.</li>
      <li><strong>GE.</strong> Same vent-first pattern. Hot-surface igniter on gas models can produce intermittent long cycles when it's getting tired.</li>
      <li><strong>Samsung.</strong> DV series moisture sensors are sensitive to dryer sheet residue. Year 5+ Samsung dryers often need sensor cleaning along with vent clearance.</li>
      <li><strong>LG.</strong> SmartDiagnosis on LG dryers often reports "low airflow" before the user notices long cycles. We confirm with anemometer.</li>
      <li><strong>Electrolux, Frigidaire (Electrolux family).</strong> Heating element degradation pattern at year 7 to 9 typical. Vent and element together is the standard repair.</li>
      <li><strong>Bosch (USA dryer line plus 800 Series condenser).</strong> Condenser dryers don't have a wall vent, but they have a condenser unit that needs separate cleaning. We cover condenser dryer service on the parent pillar.</li>
      <li><strong>Miele, Thermador.</strong> Premium tier. Heat pump models on this tier need different diagnostic (compressor and refrigerant circuit) which we cover on the parent pillar.</li>
      <li><strong>Speed Queen.</strong> Built tougher. Long-cycle calls are almost always vent-only. Heating components last 12+ years.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Long-cycle and vent clearance questions.</h2>

